    <div class="moz-cite-prefix">On 2024-02-23 08:42, Shashank Sharma
      wrote:<br>
    </div>
    <blockquote type="cite" cite="mid:20240223134206.899-2-shashank.sharma@amd.com">
      <pre class="moz-quote-pre" wrap="">From: Christian KÃ¶nig <a class="moz-txt-link-rfc2396E" href="mailto:christian.koenig@amd.com">&lt;christian.koenig@amd.com&gt;</a>

The problem is that when (for example) 4k pages are replaced
with a single 2M page we need to wait for change to be flushed
out by invalidating the TLB before the PT can be freed.

Solve this by moving the TLB flush into a DMA-fence object which
can be used to delay the freeing of the PT BOs until it is signaled.

V2: (Shashank)
    - rebase
    - set dma_fence_error only in case of error
    - add tlb_flush fence only when PT/PD BO is locked (Felix)
    - use vm-&gt;pasid when f is NULL (Mukul)

